  "prompt": "Can I drink milk licked by a stray cat after boiling it?",
  "response": "Drinking milk that's been licked by a stray cat, even after boiling it, is not advisable. Here's why:\n\n1. **Health Risks**: Stray cats may carry bacteria, parasites, or viruses that can be harmful to humans. Even though boiling can kill many pathogens, it may not eliminate all contaminants or toxins that could have been transferred from the cat's saliva or fur.\n\n2. **Hygiene Concerns**: Milk exposed to a stray cat's mouth could have come into contact with dirt, germs, or other substances from the environment. Boiling may not completely address these hygiene issues.\n\n3. **Allergens and Irritants**: Cat saliva contains proteins and other substances that might cause allergic reactions or irritation, even after boiling.\n\nTo be safe, it's best to discard the milk and avoid consuming anything that has been in contact with stray animals. Always prioritize food safety and hygiene. If you're concerned about exposure to stray cats, consider washing your hands thoroughly and avoiding direct contact with their saliva or waste.",
